<headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued June 07 at 11:36PM CDT until June 08 at 12:15AM CDT by NWS Amarillo</headline>
<description>...A SEVERE THUNDERSTORM WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 1215 AM CDT
FOR SOUTHWESTERN BEAVER...SOUTHEASTERN TEXAS AND NORTH CENTRAL
OCHILTREE COUNTIES...
At 1136 PM CDT, a severe thunderstorm was located 5 miles south of
Adams, or 20 miles east of Guymon, moving east at 30 mph.
HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and quarter size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Minor damage to roofs, siding, and trees is possible. Hail
damage to vehicles is expected.
Locations impacted include...
Hardesty, Bryans Corner, Adams and Boyd.
HAIL THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX HAIL SIZE...1.00IN
WIND THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX WIND GUST...60 MPH</description>
<instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
